latestPosts.caption:
Dreams do come true: HEROINE

Since I was a kid, I’ve always been teased for dressing up a little extra or wearing makeup just to hang out with friends or go out to play in mud. I’d hear, “Arey, tu toh heroine hai chalta hai,” and it used to make me smile,and I think everyone around me manifested it for me. Deep down, I always knew 
I was the heroine of my own life.

From a young age, I dreamt of being where I am today, but let me tell you, it hasn’t been easy. I’ve faced more failures than successes in my career, and OMG it is stressful but I’ve never given up. In 2025, it will mark a decade of me being a model and chasing my dreams. A whole freaking 10 years!

And then, in 2024, I finally became the heroine in the truest sense—when I did my first movie. The experience was surreal, so different from anything I’d ever imagined. The little girl in me was screaming and crying in happiness. 

So here’s my message to you all:
No matter how tough the journey gets, if you follow your heart, the end result will be worth it. Yes, I haven’t made as much money as I thought I would, and I don’t own a car or a house like some of my friends. But I hustle every single day and I absolutely love what I do. Not a single day of work has been without joy till date. 

Will I buy a house or a car someday? Yes, I will. But this journey—the one of following my passion, my heart, and my work it’s been more fulfilling than anything material.

Thank you, 2024, for bringing me all of this. And to my loved ones
 This journey wouldn’t have been possible without your support. 
Can’t wait for 2025 🤍

latestPosts.caption:
MY SON 🤍

I know I’m your maasi, but to me, you are so much more you are my firstborn, and you always will be. You may not have grown in my womb for nine months, but from the moment you entered this world, you took your place even closer in my heart.

I am not just your maasi, I am your safe place. Your second mother in spirit. The person who could calm your cries, the one you trusted with your whole little heart. And to this day, that bond is unshakable.

You’re my son in every way that matters. You’re the one who made me a MAASI, maa jaisi. And this feeling, this connection, it’s something words can barely hold. It’s deep. It’s different. It’s beautiful. And it will always be ours.

You’ll always be my special boy the first soul who showed me this kind of fierce, nurturing love. I’ll always be the one you can run to when you need to escape the world, or just your parents 😂 when you need to laugh, feel free, and be unapologetically yourself. I’ll be your cool aunt, yes but more than that, I’ll be your forever person. The one who gets you, holds space for you, and loves you beyond words.

Thank you for choosing me, for making me maasi. Today is not just your birthday but also my BIRTH DAY AS MASI 
You’ll always be my heart’s first home.

With all the love in the world,
Your forever Maasi

latestPosts.caption:
From then to now 🥹✨
Swipe to see 10 years of friendship wrapped in two pictures — one from when we were just two excited young girls at a pageant, and one from a recent catch-up that felt like no time had passed. 💫

We don’t see each other every day, we’ve grown into two different people chasing two very different careers in the same modeling world — but somehow, the bond stuck. It’s the kind of friendship that doesn’t need constant check-ins to stay real. Just two souls who vibed back then and still do, in our own sweet, effortless way.

It’s such a rare thing to have someone from your work field who’s seen your glow-up from the very beginning. From tiaras and backstage chaos to now — grown, evolving, still connected. 💖

Here’s to friendships that don’t follow the rules but still feel like home. 🥂👯‍♀️

PS- this time our moms also tagged along with us 🤍
